jervis.remotes
[Groovy] Class GitHub

java.lang.Object
  jervis.remotes.GitHub

class GitHub
extends Object

A simple class to interact with the GitHub API for only the parts I need.

Sample usage

import jervis.remotes.GitHub
def x = new GitHub()
println "Print each branch."
x.branches('samrocketman/jervis').each{ println it }
println "Print the contents of .travis.yml from the master branch."
println x.getFile('samrocketman/jervis','.travis.yml','master')

Property Detail

gh_api

String gh_api
URL to the GitHub API. For GitHub Enterprise it should be gh_web + "api/v3/". Default: https://api.github.com/

gh_clone

String gh_clone
The base clone URI in which repositories will be cloned. Default: git://github.com/

gh_token

String gh_token
The API token, which can be used to communicate with GitHub using authentication. Default: null

gh_web

String gh_web
URL to the GitHub web interface. Default: https://github.com/

 
Method Detail

branches

List branches(String project)
Get a list of branches for a project. This is meant to be a standard function for Jervis to interact with remotes. All remotes are required to have this function.
Parameters:
project - A GitHub project including the org. e.g. "samrocketman/jervis"
Returns:
A List where each element is a branch in the project.

getCloneUrl

String getCloneUrl()
Get the contents of gh_clone. This is meant to be a standard function for Jervis to interact with remotes. All remotes are required to have this function.
Returns:
The contents of gh_clone.

getFile

String getFile(String project, String file_path, String ref)
Get the contents of a file from a project. This is meant to be a standard function for Jervis to interact with remotes. All remotes are required to have this function.
returns:
A String which contains the contents of the file requested.
Parameters:
project - A GitHub project including the org. e.g. "samrocketman/jervis"
file_path - A path to a file relative to the root of the Git repository. e.g. ".travis.yml"
ref - A git reference such as a branch, tag, or SHA1 hash. e.g. "master"

getWebUrl

String getWebUrl()
Get the contents of gh_web. This is meant to be a standard function for Jervis to interact with remotes. All remotes are required to have this function.
Returns:
The contents of gh_web.

toString

String toString()
Get a human readable string for this type of remote. This is meant to be a standard function for Jervis to interact with remotes. All remotes are required to have this function.
Returns:
A human readable String for this type of remote. Value returned will be either "GitHub" or "GitHub Enterprise" depending on whether or not gh_web has been set.
